High-Level Flow

          ┌──────────────┐
          │   Frontend   │
          │ (Dashboard)  │
          └──────┬───────┘
                 │
                 │ HTTP Requests (fetch metrics)
                 ▼
        ┌──────────────────┐
        │    FastAPI App   │
        │  (Backend API)   │
        └────────┬─────────┘
                 │
        ┌────────▼─────────┐
        │    Middleware    │
        │ (Request Logger) │
        └────────┬─────────┘
                 │
                 ▼
        ┌──────────────────┐
        │     SQLite DB    │
        │  dashboard.db    │
        └──────────────────┘

////////////////////////////////////////////////
Request Lifecycle (What Happens Per Request)

1. Client sends request (GET /health)
2. Middleware starts timer
3. Endpoint processes request
4. Middleware stops timer
5. Request data saved to database
6. Response returned to client

////////////////////////////////////////////////
Database Model

Table: api_requests

+-------------------+
| id                |
| timestamp         |
| method            |
| path              |
| status_code       |
| response_time_ms  |
+-------------------+
Each row = one request that happened.


////////////////////////////////////////////////
Dashboard Data Flow

User opens dashboard
        ↓
Frontend calls /metrics/summary
        ↓
FastAPI queries SQLite
        ↓
Aggregated data returned as JSON
        ↓
Frontend renders charts

